<br>
Obviously, there needs to be some changes, but it is both difficult and unpopular to enforce parenting skills. Instead, we have a society that uses the electronic babysitter and has teachers who are expected to not only teach reading and writing, but morals to little Johnny as well. Oh, and the teachers usually have to be mindreaders as well since the parent's don't both telling them what morals are supposed to be taught either.<br>
<br>
Personally, I find it interesting that countries like Germany actually recognize being a stay at home mother as a profession and provide a token salary ($300/month if I remember correctly) to help support this decision. Should we be surprized that their percentage of crimes by youths are less?<br>
<br>
